Interface Queue<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue

    public interface Queue<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    The interface for a generic Queue collection whose elements are of type T.

      • getCapacity

        int getCapacity()
        Returns the number of elements the queue is currently able to hold. In the case of a dynamic queue, every time the number of elements increases beyond the queue's capacity, the capacity is doubled.
        Returns:
        the capacity of the queue

      • getNumElements

        Returns the current number of elements stored in the queue.

      • getElements

        java.util.List<T> getElements()
        Returns a list view of all elements of the queue, ordered from front to rear of the queue. Changes to this view are NOT reflected in the original queue.
        Returns:
        a list view of all elements of the queue.

      • getElementsByCriteria

        java.util.List<T> getElementsByCriteria(java.util.function.Predicate<T> criteria)
        Returns a list of elements, ordered from front to rear of the queue, that satisfy the criteria passed as argument to this function. If the given criteria is null, it returns all elements in the queue, ordered from front to rear.
        Parameters:
        criteria - a functional interface or lambda function used in evaluating whether an element should be included in the query results. If a null value is passed, all elements are returned.
        Returns:
        a list of queue elements satisfying the given criteria.
